-- Allianz, Generali Agree to Buy Additional 20% Stake in Milan's CityLife
-- Sonia Sirletti
-- 2010-06-14T08:33:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/allianz-generali-agree-to-buy-additional-20-stake-in-milan-s-citylife.html

          
          
             Allianz SE and Assicurazioni
Generali SpA agreed to buy an additional 20 percent stake in
Milan real estate project CityLife from Rome construction
company Lamaro Appaliti, according to an e-mailed statement. The
two insurers will pay 45 million euros. Generali will purchase
15 percent and Allianz 5 percent.  
